# CLAUDE.local.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code specific to your local development environment.
Copy this file to `CLAUDE.local.md` and fill in the details for your setup.

## Local Environment

I use **Docker** / **Homestead** (delete as appropriate) for local development.

---

## Docker Setup

### Remoting into the container

```bash
# Replace <container-name> with your container name (e.g. "website")
sail <container-name> bash

# Or using docker directly:
docker exec -it <container-name> bash
```

Once inside the container, the working directory is `/var/www/html` (or wherever the project is mounted).

### Running backend commands

All `php artisan` and `composer` commands must be run inside the container:

```bash
sail <container-name> bash
php artisan test
composer lint
```

---

## Homestead Setup

### Remoting into the VM

```bash
cd ~/Homestead
vagrant ssh
cd /home/vagrant/code/<project-directory>
```

### Running backend commands

All `php artisan` and `composer` commands must be run inside the VM:

```bash
cd ~/Homestead && vagrant ssh
cd /home/vagrant/code/<project-directory>
php artisan test
composer lint
```

---

## Notes

- Frontend commands (`npm run dev`, `npm run build`) are run on the **host machine**, not inside the container/VM.
- Unit tests must be run inside the container/VM — see the Backend section of `CLAUDE.md` for the full command list.
